\begin_layout Subsection*
b.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The utility is given by:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(c_{t},c_{t+1})=c_{t}+\frac{1}{\rho}c_{t+1}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As 
\begin_inset Formula $f(k_{t})=Ak_{t}^{\alpha}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta=1$
\end_inset

 and technology and population are constant, we can write:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{t}=w_{t}-s_{t}=f(k_{t})-f'(k_{t})k_{t}-s_{t}=Ak_{t}^{\alpha}-\alpha Ak_{t}^{\alpha-1}k_{t}-s_{t}=(1-\alpha)Ak_{t}^{\alpha}-s_{t}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
c_{t+1}=R_{t+1}k_{t+1}=f'(k_{t+1})k_{t+1}=f'(s_{t})s_{t}=\alpha As_{t}^{\alpha}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore we can rewrite the utility as a function of 
\begin_inset Formula $s_{t}$
\end_inset

 (with all other variables being exogenous):
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(s_{t})=(1-\alpha)Ak_{t}^{\alpha}-s_{t}+\frac{\alpha As_{t}^{\alpha}}{\rho}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The corner solutions are:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s_{t}=0\Rightarrow\bar{k}=0
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
s_{t}=w_{c}\Rightarrow u(s_{t})=\frac{\alpha A[(1-\alpha)Ak_{t}^{\alpha}]^{\alpha}}{\rho}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Opitmizing a non-corner choice leads to:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\partial u}{\partial s}=-1+\frac{\alpha^{2}A}{\rho}s_{t}^{\alpha-1}=0\Rightarrow s_{t}=\sqrt[\alpha-1]{\frac{\rho}{\alpha^{2}A}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Meaning the dynamical system is given by: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
k_{t+1}=max\left\{ \sqrt[\alpha-1]{\frac{\rho}{\alpha^{2}A}},\frac{\alpha A[(1-\alpha)Ak_{t}^{\alpha}]^{\alpha}}{\rho}\right\} 
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The steady state is characterized by consumption in the first period, if
 and only if:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{\alpha A[(1-\alpha)Ak_{t}^{\alpha}]^{\alpha}}{\rho}<\sqrt[\alpha-1]{\frac{\rho}{\alpha^{2}A}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
meaning each individual would gain more utility by consuming some of its
 income in the first period, rather than saving it all for the next one.
\end_layout

